<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 02 at 8:54PM CST  by NWS Chicago</headline>
<description>...Lake Effect Snow Accumulations Likely in Eastern Lake County
Thursday...
Lake effect snow showers are likely to move into portions of
eastern Lake County during Thursday morning. The snow showers
will produce light accumulations, possibly up to 3 inches, most
favored in the far southeast part of the county toward Deerfield,
Highland Park, and Lake Forest.
Plan for potential extra travel time during the day Thursday,
especially in the eastern portion of the county.</description>
